{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I grew up on a small farm in Missouri."},{"time":4000,"text":"We lived on less than a dollar a day"},{"time":6000,"text":"for about 15 years."},{"time":8000,"text":"I got a scholarship, went to university,"},{"time":11000,"text":"studied international agriculture, studied anthropology,"},{"time":14000,"text":"and decided I was going to give back."},{"time":16000,"text":"I was going to work with small farmers."},{"time":18000,"text":"I was going to help alleviate poverty."},{"time":20000,"text":"I was going to work on international development,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and then I took a turn"},{"time":26000,"text":"and ended up here."},{"time":29000,"text":"Now, if you get a Ph.D., and you decide not to teach,"},{"time":31000,"text":"you don't always end up in a place like this."},{"time":33000,"text":"It's a choice. You might end up driving a taxicab."},{"time":36000,"text":"You could be in New York."},{"time":40000,"text":"What I found was,"},{"time":42000,"text":"I started working with refugees and famine victims --"},{"time":45000,"text":"small farmers, all, or nearly all --"},{"time":48000,"text":"who had been dispossessed and displaced."},{"time":52000,"text":"Now, what I'd been trained to do"},{"time":55000,"text":"was methodological research on such people."},{"time":58000,"text":"So I did it: I found out how many women"},{"time":61000,"text":"had been raped en route to these camps."},{"time":64000,"text":"I found out how many people had been put in jail,"},{"time":67000,"text":"how many family members had been killed."},{"time":70000,"text":"I assessed how long they were going to stay"},{"time":72000,"text":"and how much it would take to feed them."},{"time":74000,"text":"And I got really good at predicting"},{"time":76000,"text":"how many body bags you would need"},{"time":78000,"text":"for the people who were going to die in these camps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"Now this is God's work, but it's not my work."},{"time":84000,"text":"It's not the work I set out to do."},{"time":90000,"text":"So I was at a Grateful Dead benefit concert on the rainforests"},{"time":93000,"text":"in 1988."},{"time":96000,"text":"I met a guy -- the guy on the left."},{"time":99000,"text":"His name was Ben."},{"time":101000,"text":"He said, \"What can I do to save the rainforests?\""},{"time":103000,"text":"I said, \"Well, Ben, what do you do?\""},{"time":105000,"text":"\"I make ice cream.\""},{"time":107000,"text":"So I said, \"Well, you've got to make"},{"time":109000,"text":"a rainforest ice cream."},{"time":111000,"text":"And you've got to use nuts from the rainforests"},{"time":113000,"text":"to show that forests are worth more as forests"},{"time":115000,"text":"than they are as pasture.\""},{"time":118000,"text":"He said, \"Okay.\""},{"time":120000,"text":"Within a year,"},{"time":122000,"text":"Rainforest Crunch was on the shelves."},{"time":124000,"text":"It was a great success."},{"time":126000,"text":"We did our first million-dollars-worth of trade"},{"time":129000,"text":"by buying on 30 days and selling on 21."},{"time":132000,"text":"That gets your adrenaline going."},{"time":135000,"text":"Then we had a four and a half million-dollar line of credit"},{"time":137000,"text":"because we were credit-worthy at that point."},{"time":140000,"text":"We had 15 to 20, maybe 22 percent"},{"time":142000,"text":"of the global Brazil-nut market."},{"time":144000,"text":"We paid two to three times more than anybody else."},{"time":147000,"text":"Everybody else raised their prices to the gatherers of Brazil nuts"},{"time":150000,"text":"because we would buy it otherwise."},{"time":154000,"text":"A great success."},{"time":156000,"text":"50 companies signed up, 200 products came out,"},{"time":159000,"text":"generated 100 million in sales."},{"time":164000,"text":"It failed."},{"time":166000,"text":"Why did it fail?"},{"time":168000,"text":"Because the people who were gathering Brazil nuts"},{"time":170000,"text":"weren't the same people who were cutting the forests."},{"time":173000,"text":"And the people who made money from Brazil nuts"},{"time":176000,"text":"were not the people who made money from cutting the forests."},{"time":179000,"text":"We were attacking the wrong driver."},{"time":181000,"text":"We needed to be working on beef."},{"time":183000,"text":"We needed to be working on lumber."},{"time":185000,"text":"We needed to be working on soy --"},{"time":187000,"text":"things that we were not focused on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"So let's go back to Sudan."},{"time":192000,"text":"I often talk to refugees:"},{"time":194000,"text":"\"Why was it that the West didn't realize"},{"time":197000,"text":"that famines are caused by policies and politics,"},{"time":199000,"text":"not by weather?\""},{"time":201000,"text":"And this farmer said to me, one day,"},{"time":204000,"text":"something that was very profound."},{"time":206000,"text":"He said, \"You can't wake a person who's pretending to sleep.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":211000,"text":"Okay. Fast forward."},{"time":214000,"text":"We live on a planet."},{"time":217000,"text":"There's just one of them."},{"time":219000,"text":"We've got to wake up to the fact"},{"time":221000,"text":"that we don't have any more"},{"time":223000,"text":"and that this is a finite planet."},{"time":225000,"text":"We know the limits of the resources we have."},{"time":228000,"text":"We may be able to use them differently."},{"time":230000,"text":"We may have some innovative, new ideas."},{"time":232000,"text":"But in general, this is what we've got."},{"time":234000,"text":"There's no more of it."},{"time":237000,"text":"There's a basic equation that we can't get away from."},{"time":240000,"text":"Population times consumption"},{"time":242000,"text":"has got to have some kind of relationship to the planet,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and right now, it's a simple \"not equal.\""},{"time":249000,"text":"Our work shows that we're living"},{"time":251000,"text":"at about 1.3 planets."},{"time":253000,"text":"Since 1990,"},{"time":255000,"text":"we crossed the line"},{"time":257000,"text":"of being in a sustainable relationship to the planet."},{"time":260000,"text":"Now we're at 1.3."},{"time":262000,"text":"If we were farmers, we'd be eating our seed."},{"time":265000,"text":"For bankers, we'd be living off the principal, not the interest."},{"time":268000,"text":"This is where we stand today."},{"time":271000,"text":"A lot of people like to point"},{"time":274000,"text":"to some place else as the cause of the problem."},{"time":277000,"text":"It's always population growth."},{"time":279000,"text":"Population growth's important,"},{"time":281000,"text":"but it's also about how much each person consumes."},{"time":285000,"text":"So when the average American"},{"time":287000,"text":"consumes 43 times as much"},{"time":290000,"text":"as the average African,"},{"time":293000,"text":"we've got to think that consumption is an issue."},{"time":295000,"text":"It's not just about population,"},{"time":297000,"text":"and it's not just about them; it's about us."},{"time":301000,"text":"But it's not just about people;"},{"time":303000,"text":"it's about lifestyles."},{"time":305000,"text":"There's very good evidence --"},{"time":307000,"text":"again, we don't necessarily have"},{"time":309000,"text":"a peer-reviewed methodology"},{"time":311000,"text":"that's bulletproof yet --"},{"time":313000,"text":"but there's very good evidence"},{"time":315000,"text":"that the average cat in Europe"},{"time":317000,"text":"has a larger environmental footprint in its lifetime"},{"time":320000,"text":"than the average African."},{"time":323000,"text":"You think that's not an issue going forward?"},{"time":326000,"text":"You think that's not a question"},{"time":328000,"text":"as to how we should be using the Earth's resources?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"Let's go back and visit our equation."},{"time":333000,"text":"In 2000, we had six billion people on the planet."},{"time":336000,"text":"They were consuming what they were consuming --"},{"time":338000,"text":"let's say one unit of consumption each."},{"time":340000,"text":"We have six billion units of consumption."},{"time":343000,"text":"By 2050,"},{"time":345000,"text":"we're going to have nine billion people -- all the scientists agree."},{"time":348000,"text":"They're all going to consume twice as much as they currently do --"},{"time":351000,"text":"scientists, again, agree --"},{"time":353000,"text":"because income is going to grow in developing countries"},{"time":356000,"text":"five times what it is today --"},{"time":358000,"text":"on global average, about [2.9]."},{"time":360000,"text":"So we're going to have 18 billion units of consumption."},{"time":364000,"text":"Who have you heard talking lately"},{"time":367000,"text":"that's said we have to triple production"},{"time":369000,"text":"of goods and services?"},{"time":371000,"text":"But that's what the math says."},{"time":373000,"text":"We're not going to be able to do that."},{"time":375000,"text":"We can get productivity up."},{"time":377000,"text":"We can get efficiency up."},{"time":379000,"text":"But we've also got to get consumption down."},{"time":383000,"text":"We need to use less"},{"time":385000,"text":"to make more."},{"time":387000,"text":"And then we need to use less again."},{"time":389000,"text":"And then we need to consume less."},{"time":391000,"text":"All of those things are part of that equation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"But it basically raises a fundamental question:"},{"time":397000,"text":"should consumers have a choice"},{"time":399000,"text":"about sustainability, about sustainable products?"},{"time":402000,"text":"Should you be able to buy a product that's sustainable"},{"time":404000,"text":"sitting next to one that isn't,"},{"time":406000,"text":"or should all the products on the shelf be sustainable?"},{"time":411000,"text":"If they should all be sustainable on a finite planet,"},{"time":414000,"text":"how do you make that happen?"},{"time":417000,"text":"The average consumer takes 1.8 seconds in the U.S."},{"time":419000,"text":"Okay, so let's be generous."},{"time":421000,"text":"Let's say it's 3.5 seconds in Europe."},{"time":424000,"text":"How do you evaluate all the scientific data"},{"time":427000,"text":"around a product,"},{"time":429000,"text":"the data that's changing on a weekly, if not a daily, basis?"},{"time":432000,"text":"How do you get informed?"},{"time":434000,"text":"You don't."},{"time":438000,"text":"Here's a little question."},{"time":440000,"text":"From a greenhouse gas perspective,"},{"time":442000,"text":"is lamb produced in the U.K."},{"time":445000,"text":"better than lamb produced in New Zealand,"},{"time":447000,"text":"frozen and shipped to the U.K.?"},{"time":450000,"text":"Is a bad feeder lot operation for beef"},{"time":453000,"text":"better or worse than"},{"time":456000,"text":"a bad grazing operation for beef?"},{"time":458000,"text":"Do organic potatoes"},{"time":460000,"text":"actually have fewer toxic chemicals"},{"time":462000,"text":"used to produce them"},{"time":464000,"text":"than conventional potatoes?"},{"time":466000,"text":"In every single case,"},{"time":468000,"text":"the answer is \"it depends.\""},{"time":470000,"text":"It depends on who produced it and how,"},{"time":473000,"text":"in every single instance."},{"time":475000,"text":"And there are many others."},{"time":477000,"text":"How is a consumer going to walk through this minefield?"},{"time":479000,"text":"They're not."},{"time":481000,"text":"They may have a lot of opinions about it,"},{"time":483000,"text":"but they're not going to be terribly informed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486000,"text":"Sustainability has got to be a pre-competitive issue."},{"time":489000,"text":"It's got to be something we all care about."},{"time":494000,"text":"And we need collusion."},{"time":496000,"text":"We need groups to work together that never have."},{"time":499000,"text":"We need Cargill to work with Bunge."},{"time":502000,"text":"We need Coke to work with Pepsi."},{"time":505000,"text":"We need Oxford to work with Cambridge."},{"time":507000,"text":"We need Greenpeace to work with WWF."},{"time":509000,"text":"Everybody's got to work together --"},{"time":511000,"text":"China and the U.S."},{"time":513000,"text":"We need to begin to manage this planet"},{"time":515000,"text":"as if our life depended on it,"},{"time":517000,"text":"because it does,"},{"time":519000,"text":"it fundamentally does."},{"time":521000,"text":"But we can't do everything."},{"time":523000,"text":"Even if we get everybody working on it,"},{"time":525000,"text":"we've got to be strategic."},{"time":527000,"text":"We need to focus on the where,"},{"time":529000,"text":"the what and the who."},{"time":531000,"text":"So, the where:"},{"time":533000,"text":"We've identified 35 places globally that we need to work."},{"time":535000,"text":"These are the places that are the richest in biodiversity"},{"time":538000,"text":"and the most important from an ecosystem function point-of-view."},{"time":541000,"text":"We have to work in these places."},{"time":543000,"text":"We have to save these places if we want a chance in hell"},{"time":546000,"text":"of preserving biodiversity as we know it."},{"time":551000,"text":"We looked at the threats to these places."},{"time":553000,"text":"These are the 15 commodities"},{"time":555000,"text":"that fundamentally pose the biggest threats"},{"time":557000,"text":"to these places"},{"time":559000,"text":"because of deforestation,"},{"time":561000,"text":"soil loss, water use, pesticide use,"},{"time":564000,"text":"over-fishing, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569000,"text":"So we've got 35 places,"},{"time":572000,"text":"we've got 15 priority commodities,"},{"time":574000,"text":"who do we work with"},{"time":576000,"text":"to change the way those commodities are produced?"},{"time":579000,"text":"Are we going to work with 6.9 billion consumers?"},{"time":583000,"text":"Let's see, that's about 7,000 languages,"},{"time":586000,"text":"350 major languages --"},{"time":588000,"text":"a lot of work there."},{"time":590000,"text":"I don't see anybody actually being able"},{"time":592000,"text":"to do that very effectively."},{"time":594000,"text":"Are we going to work with 1.5 billion producers?"},{"time":598000,"text":"Again, a daunting task."},{"time":601000,"text":"There must be a better way."},{"time":604000,"text":"300 to 500 companies"},{"time":606000,"text":"control 70 percent or more"},{"time":608000,"text":"of the trade of each of the 15 commodities"},{"time":611000,"text":"that we've identified as the most significant."},{"time":614000,"text":"If we work with those, if we change those companies"},{"time":617000,"text":"and the way they do business,"},{"time":619000,"text":"then the rest will happen automatically."},{"time":623000,"text":"So, we went through our 15 commodities."},{"time":625000,"text":"This is nine of them."},{"time":627000,"text":"We lined them up side-by-side,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and we put the names of the companies that work"},{"time":631000,"text":"on each of those."},{"time":634000,"text":"And if you go through the first 25 or 30 names"},{"time":636000,"text":"of each of the commodities,"},{"time":638000,"text":"what you begin to see is,"},{"time":640000,"text":"gosh, there's Cargill here, there's Cargill there,"},{"time":643000,"text":"there's Cargill everywhere."},{"time":645000,"text":"In fact, these names start coming up over and over again."},{"time":648000,"text":"So we did the analysis again a slightly different way."},{"time":652000,"text":"We said: if we take the top hundred companies,"},{"time":655000,"text":"what percentage"},{"time":657000,"text":"of all 15 commodities"},{"time":660000,"text":"do they touch, buy or sell?"},{"time":663000,"text":"And what we found is it's 25 percent."},{"time":667000,"text":"So 100 companies"},{"time":669000,"text":"control 25 percent of the trade"},{"time":672000,"text":"of all 15 of the most significant"},{"time":674000,"text":"commodities on the planet."},{"time":677000,"text":"We can get our arms around a hundred companies."},{"time":680000,"text":"A hundred companies, we can work with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"Why is 25 percent important?"},{"time":686000,"text":"Because if these companies demand sustainable products,"},{"time":689000,"text":"they'll pull 40 to 50 percent of production."},{"time":693000,"text":"Companies can push producers"},{"time":696000,"text":"faster than consumers can."},{"time":699000,"text":"By companies asking for this,"},{"time":701000,"text":"we can leverage production so much faster"},{"time":704000,"text":"than by waiting for consumers to do it."},{"time":706000,"text":"After 40 years, the global organic movement"},{"time":709000,"text":"has achieved 0.7 of one percent"},{"time":711000,"text":"of global food."},{"time":713000,"text":"We can't wait that long."},{"time":715000,"text":"We don't have that kind of time."},{"time":717000,"text":"We need change"},{"time":719000,"text":"that's going to accelerate."},{"time":722000,"text":"Even working with individual companies"},{"time":724000,"text":"is not probably going to get us there."},{"time":726000,"text":"We need to begin to work with industries."},{"time":729000,"text":"So we've started roundtables"},{"time":731000,"text":"where we bring together the entire value chain,"},{"time":733000,"text":"from producers"},{"time":735000,"text":"all the way to the retailers and brands."},{"time":737000,"text":"We bring in civil society, we bring in NGOs,"},{"time":739000,"text":"we bring in researchers and scientists"},{"time":741000,"text":"to have an informed discussion --"},{"time":743000,"text":"sometimes a battle royale --"},{"time":745000,"text":"to figure out what are the key impacts"},{"time":748000,"text":"of these products,"},{"time":750000,"text":"what is a global benchmark,"},{"time":751000,"text":"what's an acceptable impact,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and design standards around that."},{"time":757000,"text":"It's not all fun and games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761000,"text":"In salmon aquaculture,"},{"time":763000,"text":"we kicked off a roundtable"},{"time":765000,"text":"almost six years ago."},{"time":767000,"text":"Eight entities came to the table."},{"time":770000,"text":"We eventually got, I think, 60 percent"},{"time":772000,"text":"of global production at the table"},{"time":774000,"text":"and 25 percent of demand at the table."},{"time":777000,"text":"Three of the original eight entities were suing each other."},{"time":780000,"text":"And yet, next week, we launch"},{"time":783000,"text":"globally verified, vetted and certified"},{"time":786000,"text":"standards for salmon aquaculture."},{"time":789000,"text":"It can happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"So what brings"},{"time":801000,"text":"the different entities to the table?"},{"time":805000,"text":"It's risk and demand."},{"time":807000,"text":"For the big companies, it's reputational risk,"},{"time":809000,"text":"but more importantly,"},{"time":811000,"text":"they don't care what the price of commodities is."},{"time":813000,"text":"If they don't have commodities, they don't have a business."},{"time":816000,"text":"They care about availability,"},{"time":818000,"text":"so the big risk for them is not having product at all."},{"time":821000,"text":"For the producers,"},{"time":823000,"text":"if a buyer wants to buy something produced a certain way,"},{"time":826000,"text":"that's what brings them to the table."},{"time":828000,"text":"So it's the demand that brings them to the table."},{"time":831000,"text":"The good news is"},{"time":833000,"text":"we identified a hundred companies two years ago."},{"time":835000,"text":"In the last 18 months, we've signed agreements"},{"time":837000,"text":"with 40 of those hundred companies"},{"time":839000,"text":"to begin to work with them on their supply chain."},{"time":841000,"text":"And in the next 18 months,"},{"time":844000,"text":"we will have signed up to work with another 40,"},{"time":847000,"text":"and we think we'll get those signed as well."},{"time":849000,"text":"Now what we're doing is bringing the CEOs"},{"time":851000,"text":"of these 80 companies together"},{"time":853000,"text":"to help twist the arms of the final 20,"},{"time":856000,"text":"to bring them to the table,"},{"time":858000,"text":"because they don't like NGOs, they've never worked with NGOs,"},{"time":861000,"text":"they're concerned about this, they're concerned about that,"},{"time":863000,"text":"but we all need to be in this together."},{"time":865000,"text":"So we're pulling out all the stops."},{"time":867000,"text":"We're using whatever leverage we have to bring them to the table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"One company we're working with that's begun --"},{"time":873000,"text":"in baby steps, perhaps --"},{"time":875000,"text":"but has begun this journey on sustainability is Cargill."},{"time":878000,"text":"They've funded research that shows"},{"time":881000,"text":"that we can double global palm oil production"},{"time":883000,"text":"without cutting a single tree in the next 20 years,"},{"time":886000,"text":"and do it all in Borneo alone"},{"time":888000,"text":"by planting on land that's already degraded."},{"time":890000,"text":"The study shows that the highest net present value"},{"time":893000,"text":"for palm oil"},{"time":895000,"text":"is on land that's been degraded."},{"time":898000,"text":"They're also undertaking a study to look at"},{"time":900000,"text":"all of their supplies of palm oil"},{"time":903000,"text":"to see if they could be certified"},{"time":905000,"text":"and what they would need to change in order to become third-party certified"},{"time":908000,"text":"under a credible certification program."},{"time":912000,"text":"Why is Cargill important?"},{"time":914000,"text":"Because Cargill has 20 to 25 percent"},{"time":916000,"text":"of global palm oil."},{"time":918000,"text":"If Cargill makes a decision,"},{"time":920000,"text":"the entire palm oil industry moves,"},{"time":923000,"text":"or at least 40 or 50 percent of it."},{"time":925000,"text":"That's not insignificant."},{"time":927000,"text":"More importantly, Cargill and one other company"},{"time":929000,"text":"ship 50 percent of the palm oil"},{"time":932000,"text":"that goes to China."},{"time":934000,"text":"We don't have to change the way"},{"time":936000,"text":"a single Chinese company works"},{"time":938000,"text":"if we get Cargill to only send"},{"time":940000,"text":"sustainable palm oil to China."},{"time":943000,"text":"It's a pre-competitive issue."},{"time":945000,"text":"All the palm oil going there is good."},{"time":947000,"text":"Buy it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"Mars is also on a similar journey."},{"time":952000,"text":"Now most people understand that Mars is a chocolate company,"},{"time":955000,"text":"but Mars has made sustainability pledges"},{"time":957000,"text":"to buy only certified product for all of its seafood."},{"time":960000,"text":"It turns out Mars buys more seafood than Walmart"},{"time":962000,"text":"because of pet food."},{"time":964000,"text":"But they're doing some really interesting things around chocolate,"},{"time":967000,"text":"and it all comes from the fact"},{"time":969000,"text":"that Mars wants to be in business in the future."},{"time":972000,"text":"And what they see is that they need to"},{"time":974000,"text":"improve chocolate production."},{"time":977000,"text":"On any given plantation,"},{"time":979000,"text":"20 percent of the trees produce 80 percent of the crop,"},{"time":982000,"text":"so Mars is looking at the genome,"},{"time":984000,"text":"they're sequencing the genome of the cocoa plant."},{"time":986000,"text":"They're doing it with IBM and the USDA,"},{"time":988000,"text":"and they're putting it in the public domain"},{"time":990000,"text":"because they want everybody to have access to this data,"},{"time":993000,"text":"because they want everybody to help them"},{"time":995000,"text":"make cocoa more productive and more sustainable."},{"time":998000,"text":"What they've realized"},{"time":1000000,"text":"is that if they can identify the traits"},{"time":1002000,"text":"on productivity and drought tolerance,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"they can produce 320 percent as much cocoa"},{"time":1008000,"text":"on 40 percent of the land."},{"time":1011000,"text":"The rest of the land can be used for something else."},{"time":1014000,"text":"It's more with less and less again."},{"time":1017000,"text":"That's what the future has got to be,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and putting it in the public domain is smart."},{"time":1022000,"text":"They don't want to be an I.P. company; they want to be a chocolate company,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"but they want to be a chocolate company forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028000,"text":"Now, the price of food, many people complain about,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"but in fact, the price of food is going down,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"and that's odd because in fact,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"consumers are not paying for the true cost of food."},{"time":1039000,"text":"If you take a look just at water,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"what we see is that,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"with four very common products,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"you look at how much a farmer produced to make those products,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"and then you look at how much water input was put into them,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"and then you look at what the farmer was paid."},{"time":1055000,"text":"If you divide the amount of water"},{"time":1057000,"text":"into what the farmer was paid,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"the farmer didn't receive enough money"},{"time":1061000,"text":"to pay a decent price for water in any of those commodities."},{"time":1064000,"text":"That is an externality by definition."},{"time":1066000,"text":"This is the subsidy from nature."},{"time":1068000,"text":"Coca-Cola, they've worked a lot on water,"},{"time":1071000,"text":"but right now, they're entering into 17-year contracts"},{"time":1074000,"text":"with growers in Turkey"},{"time":1076000,"text":"to sell juice into Europe,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"and they're doing that because they want to have a product"},{"time":1081000,"text":"that's closer to the European market."},{"time":1083000,"text":"But they're not just buying the juice;"},{"time":1085000,"text":"they're also buying the carbon in the trees"},{"time":1088000,"text":"to offset the shipment costs associated with carbon"},{"time":1090000,"text":"to get the product into Europe."},{"time":1093000,"text":"There's carbon that's being bought with sugar,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"with coffee, with beef."},{"time":1098000,"text":"This is called bundling. It's bringing those externalities"},{"time":1100000,"text":"back into the price of the commodity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104000,"text":"We need to take what we've learned in private, voluntary standards"},{"time":1107000,"text":"of what the best producers in the world are doing"},{"time":1110000,"text":"and use that to inform government regulation,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"so we can shift the entire performance curve."},{"time":1116000,"text":"We can't just focus on identifying the best;"},{"time":1118000,"text":"we've got to move the rest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121000,"text":"The issue isn't what to think, it's how to think."},{"time":1124000,"text":"These companies have begun to think differently."},{"time":1126000,"text":"They're on a journey; there's no turning back."},{"time":1129000,"text":"We're all on that same journey with them."},{"time":1132000,"text":"We have to really begin to change"},{"time":1135000,"text":"the way we think about everything."},{"time":1137000,"text":"Whatever was sustainable on a planet of six billion"},{"time":1140000,"text":"is not going to be sustainable on a planet with nine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1145000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}